The paper deals with a game-theoretic model of network security, which suggests that it is most likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) category. The paper also discusses the impact of digital security breaches on social networks, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. The use of network models and the study of information spreading processes suggest that it could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Networked Systems (cs.NI) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of investments in security, which could place it in the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) category.
